research.COMPRESSOR.title=Compressor
research.COMPRESSOR.stage.1=I found plate production too wasteful for routine work, so I devised a compressor to make the process more reliable and efficient.
research.COMPRESSOR.stage.2=§lCompressor§r<BR>This device presses ingots into plates through a mechanical process. Different metals yield different plate types, including specialized variants for arcane applications.<PAGE>

research.CLOAK.title=Shadowed Cloak
research.CLOAK.stage.1=The veil of shadows whispers secrets of concealment. Its essence lies in blending with the darkness, evading prying eyes.
research.CLOAK.stage.2=The Shadowed Cloak has become an extension of your will. You now walk unseen, a phantom among mortals.


research.UNSTONE.title=Anti-Flight Stone
research.UNSTONE.stage.1=In my anti-magic studies, I discovered a peculiar stone that disrupts flight enchantments. When placed, the Anti-Flight Stone creates a field that forcibly suppresses magical flight.
research.UNSTONE.stage.2=§lAnti-Flight Stone§r<BR>This warded stone anchors the air around it, projecting a 3x3 chunk field that suppresses magical flight. Wings, levitation, and other airborne tricks fail inside its reach, making it a stubborn guardian for restricted places.<PAGE>§lFlight Stone§r<BR>By reversing the same pattern, the Flight Stone lends lift instead of stealing it. It is built from the anti-flight form and turns that grounded force into controlled ascent.

research.DUPLICATOR.title=Mattery Duplicator
research.DUPLICATOR.stage.1=When the Pattern Crafter block reached its limits, I drafted a new machine: one that harnesses Mattery essence to replicate matter directly.
research.DUPLICATOR.stage.2=§lMattery Duplicator§r<BR>The Duplicator absorbs Mattery essence from nearby containers and uses it to replicate items placed in the grid. The process only begins when enough essence is available, so I must monitor reserves carefully.<PAGE>

research.OREAQUA.title=Ores
research.OREAQUA.stage.1=§oAquareia Ore§r<IMG>thaumicforever:textures/misc/aqa.png:0:0:256:256:0.5</IMG>I have confirmed that Aquareia Ore is a rare magical mineral found deep in the *Magical Forest*. Most veins appear between Y 28 and Y 32, usually in clusters of 2 to 6 blocks, where the forest's natural magic is strongest.

entity.ItemFrame.name=Item Frame

research.FOOD.title=Special Food
research.FOOD.stage.1=I have discovered that food can offer far more than simple nourishment. Certain ingredient combinations awaken unusual effects.
research.FOOD.stage.2=My tests confirm that some meals grant extraordinary abilities. With proper ingredients, I can craft food fit for arcane fieldwork.


research.ANGRY_SKELET.title=Angry Skeleton
research.ANGRY_SKELET.stage.1=During my explorations, I stumbled upon a strange variation of a skeleton. Unlike the common undead warriors, this one displayed unusual aggression and speed, as if fueled by an unquenchable rage. It seems to possess higher durability and intelligence, dodging attacks with unexpected precision. Could it be a result of some dark magic, or is it simply an evolved form of an ordinary skeleton? Further study is required to unravel the mystery behind its origin.<BR>Upon examining its remains, I noticed something peculiar about its bones. They are significantly denser and stronger than those of regular skeletons. This discovery leads me to wonder—could these bones be used to forge a weapon, perhaps one infused with the same unrelenting rage that fueled this creature?
research.VAMPIRE_BAT.title=Vampire Bat
research.VAMPIRE_BAT.stage.1=In the Erie's pale daylight, I observed a bat that should not exist in such open hours. It hunts not in blind panic, but with intent, striking in short bursts and leaving wounds that continue to bleed after the bite.<BR>The creature carries a tainted resonance of life and death at once: unmistakably undead, yet restless and predatory. If this strain spreads, it could become a serious threat to any thaumaturge who relies on attrition and prolonged fights.
research.VAMPIRE_BAT.addenda.1=I translated the bat's hemorrhagic behavior into infusion geometry. By stabilizing life-and-death resonance inside a ruby matrix, I forged a ring that sustains vampirism while worn.
research.RESEARCHCLEANFT.title=Lucid Mind Distillation
research.RESEARCHCLEANFT.stage.1=Aura phials hold cognitive patterns with unusual stability. By binding Mind and Order in a controlled crucible cycle, I can distill a reagent that dampens mental static and restores disciplined thought.
research.RESEARCHCLEANFT.stage.2=I can now distill §lLucidity Elixir§r in the crucible using an aura phial as the catalyst. The compound clears arcane haze, settles intrusive resonance, and returns focus after heavy thaumaturgic strain.

research.DeconstructionTable.title=Deconstruction Table
research.DeconstructionTable.stage.1=I constructed a Deconstruction Table to break common items into base components and study the hidden arcane traits within. Its ability to extract curios makes it indispensable when mundane matter must be analyzed.
research.DeconstructionTable.stage.2=§lDeconstruction Table§r<BR>Matter remembers. With careful pressure and a little controlled ruin, this table peels those memories from an item and presses them into a Knowledge Fragment.<BR>Any object bearing registered aspects may be sacrificed. The richer its nature, the richer the fragment. Right-click the fragment to reclaim the aspects.

