research.golem_core_fish.title=Control Seal: Fishing
research.golem_core_fish.stage.1=This seal allows golems to engage in fishing by reacting to movement within nearby bodies of water, much like a simple predator. At first, their behavior is crude—they lash out at anything that stirs the surface.<BR>However, I have found that by fine-tuning the core's configuration, the golem can be taught to focus on specific targets, even distinguishing between different types of fish.
research.golem_core_fish.stage.2=I have refined the seal further by synchronizing it with the natural flow of water. As a result, golems now react more precisely and efficiently when fish are nearby.<BR>More intriguingly, it appears possible to apply a minor enchantment to the core, enhancing the likelihood of capturing rare aquatic specimens. With additional adjustments, this seal could become a reliable method of gathering valuable resources from the depths.
research.golem_core_fish.addenda.1=I can now craft an advanced version of this seal. It supports category control for catches (fish, junk, treasure), optional redstone signaling, and item filtering via white/black list.<PAGE>With finer logic matrices, this advanced seal can be tuned for very specific fishing workflows. It also requires a smarter golem core to operate at full efficiency.

research.ORB.title=Orb
research.ORBNONE.stage.1=I keep finding condensed masses of raw magic that solidify into what scholars call an "orb." Each one resonates with a distinct force and changes how nearby aura behaves. Whether natural or crafted, these orbs still hide untapped potential.
research.ORBTAINT.amber=This orb carries concentrated corruption. Its output is unstable, and dark residue occasionally leaks from the shell, infecting nearby matter. Careful study may reveal safer containment methods.
research.ORBCRIMS.amber=This orb emits a deep crimson radiance bound to ancient blood-tinged power. In its presence the air grows heavy and the silence feels watchful, as if the artifact itself listens.

research.TAINT_AMULET.title=Amulet of Taint
research.TAINT_AMULET.stage.1=§bTaint Amulet§r<BR><IMG>thaumicforever:textures/items/taint_amulet.png:0:0:256:256:0.13</IMG><BR>This artifact carries a stabilizing charge that shields me from Taint poisoning. More strangely, tainted creatures seem to ignore the wearer, as if the amulet cloaks them in familiar corruption.<BR>Its true cost remains unclear: does it ward the Taint, or merely hide me while binding me to it?

research.seal_golem_core_essentia.title=Control Seal: Crystal Refill
research.seal_golem_core_essentia.stage.1=Manual crystal refilling has become a constant bottleneck in my workbench routines.<BR>A simple funnel cannot solve it: crystals must be placed into the correct slots, in the correct form, and at the correct moment.<BR>I therefore began designing a control seal that can detect shortages and direct a golem to perform proper slot-aware replenishment.
research.seal_golem_core_essentia.stage.2=I have refined the seal's logic, granting it the ability to monitor the quantity of crystals present. If suitable crystals are nearby, the golem will immediately begin the refill process, minimizing any interruption in arcane operations.<BR>This seal is especially effective when used with automated systems, where maintaining a constant flow of crystals is essential without the thaumaturge’s direct involvement.

