research.TRANSDUCER.title=Node Transducer
research.TRANSDUCER.text=From dormant to unstoppable
research.TRANSDUCER.stage.1=Without §5Aura Nodes§0, thaumaturges would be powerless, but their limitations are well known: they deplete quickly and recover §eVis§0 far too slowly for large-scale work.<BR>You have discovered a dangerous method to bypass this limitation — by converting a normal node into an §6Energized Node§0.<BR>First, the node must be completely stabilized during the process. Place a §eNode Stabilizer§0 beneath the node to hold it steady.<BR>Then craft and install a §lNode Transducer§r above the stabilized node. Applying a redstone signal will begin the transformation, causing the node to rapidly lose its stored aspects.
research.TRANSDUCER.stage.2=The transformation process is slow but irreversible once complete. The node will emerge as an §6Energized Node§0, no longer storing or regenerating §eVis§0, nor allowing wands to draw from it.<BR>Instead, it will emit a constant flow of §lCV§r (centi-vis) each tick, ready to be captured by nearby §eVis Relays§0. Relays can link together to carry CV to devices like the §cInfernal Furnace§0.<BR>You may 'tune' a relay with a vis shard or wand to restrict its connections.
research.TRANSDUCER.stage.3=The CV output of an energized node is finite, so overloading it will cause power shortages. Too many devices on one source may slow or halt operations.<BR>Cutting the redstone signal will slowly revert the energized node to normal — but beware: it will return completely drained and vulnerable.<BR>Advanced thaumaturges have learned to combine transducers with Ports and stabilizers, enabling safe, long-range transfer of CV and aspects.<BR>§4Caution:§0 Any interruption during conversion may damage or destroy the node.

research.CHAINLIGHTNING.title=Focus Effect: Chain Lightning
research.CHAINLIGHTNING.stage.1=Vis is more than fire and frost. With the proper pattern I should be able to call forth a fork of raw energy that leaps between nearby creatures.<BR>By imprinting a conductive lattice around a core of §nAuram§0 and §nPraecantatio§0, the vis discharge should seek the closest targets and arc between them in rapid succession. My notes suggest keeping the stream brief to avoid instability.<BR>The effect does not break blocks, but living matter will not enjoy the experience.
research.CHAINLIGHTNING.stage.2=This effect shines when linked to §nTouch§0 or §nBolt§0. The first struck target becomes the origin and the arc will then jump to other nearby creatures several times.<BR>Range between jumps and the number of jumps are limited by the lattice's stability. In my prototype that is roughly §n3 blocks§0 per jump and up to §n5 jumps§0. Power tuning increases the damage of each strike but does not extend range.<PAGE>§nNotes§0<BR>• The arc will avoid already struck targets in the same cast.<BR>• It will not jump through the void and ignores dead or invalid targets.<BR>• Each jump consumes a small extra amount of vis from the aura.<BR>• Works well with §nScatter§0 or seeking projectiles, but bolts remain the most reliable starter for the chain.

research.f_chain.text=Examine lightning during a thunderstorm.
thaumicforever.CHAINLIGHTNING.name=Chain Lightning
thaumicforever.CHAINLIGHTNING.text=Launches a bolt of lightning that jumps between multiple enemies, dealing reduced damage with each jump.
