focus.thaumicforever.timecooldown.delay.2=2 sec
focus.thaumicforever.timecooldown.delay.4=4 sec
focus.thaumicforever.timecooldown.delay.6=6 sec
focus.thaumicforever.timecooldown.delay.8=8 sec
focus.common.range=Range
research.TIMEBOMB.title=Focus Modifier: Time Cooldown
research.TIMEBOMB.stage.1=By anchoring a cast to local temporal inertia, I can force the focus to wait before releasing the next stage. The structure remains stable only in discrete intervals.
research.TIMEBOMB.stage.2=I can now insert a timed delay modifier before an effect and choose a fixed release window of 2, 4, 6, or 8 seconds.
research.PRIMALFOCUS.title=Focus Effect: Chaos
research.PRIMALFOCUS.stage.1=I scrapped stable primal lattices and replaced them with a chaotic selector that binds arbitrary focus mediums and effects at cast time.
research.PRIMALFOCUS.stage.2=Each trigger now prepares the next chain in advance. The following cast releases that prepared combination with randomized internal settings.
research.PRIMAL_FOCI.title=Focus Effect: Chaos
research.PRIMAL_FOCI.stage.1=I scrapped stable primal lattices and replaced them with a chaotic selector that binds arbitrary focus mediums and effects at cast time.
research.PRIMAL_FOCI.stage.2=Each trigger now prepares the next chain in advance. The following cast releases that prepared combination with randomized internal settings.
research.FOCUSPRIMAL_ELEMENT.title=Focus Effect: Primal Element Chain
research.FOCUSPRIMAL_ELEMENT.stage.1=I shaped a deterministic elemental sequence instead of chaotic selection. If Thaumic Augmentation is present, the chain begins with a light water strike, then transitions into the core Thaumcraft elements.
research.FOCUSPRIMAL_ELEMENT.stage.2=The sequence now stabilizes as: Water (tier 1, TA if available), then Fire, Frost, and Earth. Its complexity is tuned to roughly 70%% of the combined Thaumcraft triad load.
