research.WANDCHARGE.title=Wand Charging Array
research.WANDCHARGE.stage.0=The standard charger is useful, but it does not account for the unstable pulse that appears when a wand is fed from dense aura pockets. I can stabilize this process by forcing vis through a tuned crystal focus and a resonant support frame.<PAGE>By shaping the flow before it reaches the wand cap, I should be able to keep charging continuous and controlled. If the calibration is correct, recharge speed will improve and vis loss from turbulence will be reduced.
research.WANDCHARGE.stage.1=The assembled charging array performs as intended: the wand now receives vis through a constrained channel rather than a raw surge. This keeps transfer steady even when nearby nodes fluctuate.<BR>The device works best when mounted near my wand workbench. With proper materials and an aquareia catalyst, the array becomes a reliable way to refill high-capacity wands between crafting sessions.<PAGE>§lCV Connection§r<BR>The charger can also accept §lCV§r from a nearby Port. A Port acts as a centi-vis conductor: it can receive CV from compatible thaumic devices and pass it into the charging array instead of relying only on local node conditions.<BR><BR>For stable setups, link Ports between the CV source and the charger, then place the final Port close enough for the charger to draw from it.<PAGE>§lWand Recharge Pedestal§r<BR>I have also completed a dedicated pedestal variant for direct wand charging. It accepts a wand directly, keeps charging stable, and is ideal for restoring large vis reserves between long crafting cycles. Like the larger array, it can benefit from a proper CV feed through Ports.
