research.STAFF_ALL.title=Additional Rods
research.STAFF_ALL.stage.0=The classic woods no longer cover all of my needs. By studying foreign schools and rare materials, I can adapt them into rods with distinct arcane behavior.
research.STAFF_ALL.stage.1=I have stabilized four advanced rod patterns for extreme use-cases.<BR>§lIchorcloth Rod§r: capacity 900; self-recharges every second, stronger at night, in the Nether, and in the End.<BR>§lAdaminitewood Rod§r: capacity 3200; no passive trick, but unmatched raw reserve for long casting chains.<BR>§lInfernal Rod§r: capacity 1200; recharges faster in the Nether, extinguishes fire, and removes Wither from the bearer.<BR>§lChorus Rod§r: capacity 1200; recharges faster in the End and removes Levitation.
research.CAP_MATERIAL_ADD.title=Additional Wand Caps
research.CAP_MATERIAL_ADD.stage.0=I have compiled notes on foreign cap materials, from Botania alloys to blood-bound and ember-forged components. Their behavior is irregular, but proper infusion can stabilize them.
research.CAP_MATERIAL_ADD.stage.1=This branch focuses on cross-school caps and their practical roles.<BR>§lManasteel§r: 90% vis cost, stable all-purpose cap with Praecantatio/Auram crystal discount +1.<BR>§lElementium§r: 82% vis cost, stronger elemental alignment with Aer/Ignis/Aqua/Terra crystal discount +1.<BR>§lTerrasteel§r: 75% vis cost, high-tier mana alloy tuned for heavy casting; Praecantatio/Auram +2 and Herba +1.<BR>§lAlchemical§r: 90% vis cost, blood-attuned cap with Aqua/Victus crystal discount +1.<BR>§lDawnstone§r: 95% vis cost, ember-forged control cap with Aer/Ignis crystal discount +1.
research.STAFF_ADD.title=Exotic Rods
research.STAFF_ADD.stage.0=After mastering the classic woods, I moved on to foreign vis conduits: livingwood, dreamwood, blood, archaic matter, and other rare substrates.
research.STAFF_ADD.stage.1=These exotic rods are tuned for situational sustain and combat rhythm.<BR>§lLivingwood Rod§r: capacity 500; regenerates charge passively, stronger on natural ground (grass/dirt/leaves).<BR>§lDreamwood Rod§r: capacity 800; passive recharge every second, stronger at night and in the End.<BR>§lBlood Rod§r: capacity 850; converts a small amount of your health into wand charge (only while healthy enough).<BR>§lArchaic Rod§r: capacity 700; passive recharge, stronger in HOT/NETHER biomes.
research.NEWGOLEMANCY.title=Advanced Golemancy
research.NEWGOLEMANCY.stage.1=The first seals taught obedience, but not persistence. If golems are to serve more complex systems, I need storage and support structures that can hold intent, memory, and directed thought without collapsing into simple automation.
research.NEWGOLEMANCY.stage.2=The Big Jar is a large vessel for preserved intellect. Its reinforced glass can hold several brains at once, allowing them to remain stable enough to assist nearby devices instead of merely floating as curiosities.
research.NEWGOLEMANCY.addenda.1=Further use has revealed that the Big Jar is not powered by brains alone. Additional jarred brains increase the number of minds available, but those minds must be sustained by Mind essentia kept nearby. The jar also hungers for experience; loose experience orbs are drawn in and stored as the memories needed for longer work.<BR>When placed before a Great Research Table, the jar lends these stored thoughts to unfinished research notes. More brains and more experience make the work steadier, while a dry jar soon falls silent. I should not take my eyes off them for too long, however. Preserved minds are still minds, and some of them may yet harbour malice.
research.GREATRESEARCHTABLE.title=Great Research Table
research.GREATRESEARCHTABLE.stage.1=The workings of a research table are not limited by parchment, ink, or tools, but by the speed of thought itself. I have found that preserved brains still retain enough pattern and instinct to follow the shape of a problem, though they require a proper focus if they are to do so safely.
research.GREATRESEARCHTABLE.stage.2=By joining an old Research Table to a Greatwood Table and touching the seam with Salis Mundus, the two can be persuaded to become a larger instrument. The result is a table broad enough to hold both the work and the borrowed attention required to finish it.<BR>If scribing tools and an unfinished research note are placed within it, and a Big Jar is set before the table, the brains suspended inside the jar will slowly work through the note. More brains improve the pace, while more complex notes take longer to solve. Ink is still consumed as normal: thought without ink remains only thought.
