research.AURATOTEMS.title=Aura Totems
research.AURATOTEMS.stage.0=The §5Primal Aura§0 is a slow, heavy current below ordinary vis. Aura Totems do not charge items directly; they reshape this current between chunks so a working site can be drained, fed, or stabilized.<PAGE>Use them when a place has too much primal aura pressure, too little support for nearby thaumaturgy, or too much risk of flux during aura work. The totems are crude machines: useful, but never completely safe.
research.AURATOTEMS.stage.1=Each aura totem works with two zones: an inner zone and an outer zone. By default the inner zone is the chunk containing the totem, while the outer zone is the ring of chunks around it.<PAGE>Totem poles placed under the main block reshape these zones. Up to five poles may support one totem. The main block decides the direction of flow; the poles decide how wide and stable that flow becomes.
research.AURATOTEMS.stage.2=§lUsing Aura Totems§r<BR>An aura totem is built as a vertical structure. The main push or pull totem sits on top, while up to five pole blocks below it shape the working field. The totem does not run for free: right-click it with a vis crystal to charge it. One crystal gives 500 pulses, and the aspect inside that crystal decides which primal aura is moved.<PAGE><BR><IMG>thaumicforever:textures/research/research3.png:155:0:100:80:0.4</IMG><BR><PAGE>§lAura Totem: Push§r<BR>The push totem, or dispersal totem, drains one pulse of primal aura from the inner zone and sends it into a random chunk in the outer zone. Use it to thin a saturated work area or push pressure away from fragile thaumaturgy.<PAGE>§lAura Totem: Pull§r<BR>The pull totem reverses that motion. It drains one pulse from the outer zone and concentrates it into a random chunk in the inner zone. Use it to feed a local work site, node area, or stabilizer with a chosen primal aspect.<PAGE>§lInner Pole§r<BR>Inner poles expand the inner zone. With more inner poles, the center area becomes wider, so push totems draw from a broader center and pull totems fill a broader center.<PAGE>§lOuter Pole§r<BR>Outer poles expand the outer zone. With more outer poles, the totem reaches farther rings of chunks and pulses more often, because the flow has more paths to move through.<PAGE>§lPure Pole§r<BR>Pure poles do not expand the radius. They stabilize the current and reduce the chance that a pulse becomes flux. They are most useful when a fast or wide totem has several inner or outer poles.
