research.VOIDCHEST.title=Void Chest
research.VOIDCHEST.stage.0=Ender chests bind storage to the traveller, but that is the wrong shape for a workshop. I need a chest whose absence is the lock: a container network tied to the blocks themselves, not to the owner who opened them.
research.VOIDCHEST.stage.1=§lVoid Chest§r<BR>A Void Chest stores its contents in a shared void network. A newly placed chest creates its own network, but several chests can be joined together with an ordinary name tag.<PAGE>Right-click the first Void Chest with a name tag to copy its network data. The tag will rename itself to the chest coordinates. Right-click another Void Chest with that marked tag and it will join the same virtual inventory. The network is block-bound, so any player opening a linked chest sees the same contents.
