research.REDSTONEGENETATOR.title=Redstone Ticker
research.REDSTONEGENETATOR.stage.0=Ordinary redstone circuits are predictable, but some mechanisms benefit from unstable timing. By binding redstone dust to a simple thaumic mechanism, I can create a block that emits irregular pulses instead of a fixed signal.
research.REDSTONEGENETATOR.stage.1=§lRedstone Ticker§r<BR>The Redstone Ticker randomly changes its output strength over time. Sometimes it gives no signal at all; sometimes it emits a weak or strong pulse. It is useful for chaotic machinery, timed traps, randomizers, and devices that should not repeat with perfect rhythm.

