entity.DecoyMannequin.name=Decoy Mannequin
research.DECOYMANNEQUIN.title=Decoy Mannequin
research.DECOYMANNEQUIN.stage.0=Some experiments require a living presence, but using an actual thaumaturge as bait is inefficient and usually fatal. A reinforced mannequin can be made convincing enough for hostile creatures and nearby mechanisms to treat it as a target.
research.DECOYMANNEQUIN.stage.1=§lDecoy Mannequin§r<BR>The Decoy Mannequin is placed like an armor stand. It acts as a lure for nearby hostile mobs and maintains its area so spawners and other presence-sensitive systems continue to function around it. It is not a true person, but it is close enough to draw attention away from one.
